The United States and China have issued a joint statement on their economic relations, affirming their shared interest in promoting a strong and open global economy. Both countries recognize the importance of international financial institutions and commit to strengthening and modernizing them. They also acknowledge the role of multilateral development banks in meeting the needs of the poorest countries and commit to increasing their lending capacity. The United States and China commit to strengthening their cooperation in the International Monetary Fund (IMF) and improving its quota and governance structure. They also agree to limit the scope of their national security reviews of foreign investments and to treat all investors in a fair and equitable manner. Both countries emphasize the importance of technology and intellectual property protection and commit to conducting high-level and expert discussions on judicial reform. The statement also covers agricultural cooperation, financial market connection, and green finance.